details.string: Calling EFI Application from Boot Option

grub_cmd: menuentry Ubuntu --class ubuntu --class gnu-linux --class gnu --class os --id gnulinux-simple-bdcbe209-a589-47c6-9311-aee61f3ef2de {
	recordfail
	load_video
	gfxmode $linux_gfx_mode
	insmod gzio
	if [ x$grub_platform = xxen ]; then insmod xzio; insmod lzopio; fi
	insmod part_gpt
	insmod ext2
	search --no-floppy --fs-uuid --set=root bdcbe209-a589-47c6-9311-aee61f3ef2de
	if [ "${initrdfail}" = 1 ]; then
	  echo	'GRUB_FORCE_PARTUUID set, initrdless boot failed. Attempting with initrd.'
	  linux	/boot/vmlinuz-6.8.0-1025-gcp root=PARTUUID=b051c61f-d3ef-4e82-9463-c46f2810d974 ro  console=ttyS0,115200
	  initrd	/boot/initrd.img-6.8.0-1025-gcp
	else
	  echo	'GRUB_FORCE_PARTUUID set, attempting initrdless boot.'
	  linux	/boot/vmlinuz-6.8.0-1025-gcp root=PARTUUID=b051c61f-d3ef-4e82-9463-c46f2810d974 ro  console=ttyS0,115200 panic=-1
	fi
	initrdfail
}

grub_cmd: submenu Advanced options for Ubuntu --id gnulinux-advanced-bdcbe209-a589-47c6-9311-aee61f3ef2de {
	menuentry 'Ubuntu, with Linux 6.8.0-1025-gcp' --class ubuntu --class gnu-linux --class gnu --class os $menuentry_id_option 'gnulinux-6.8.0-1025-gcp-advanced-bdcbe209-a589-47c6-9311-aee61f3ef2de' {
		recordfail
		load_video
		gfxmode $linux_gfx_mode
		insmod gzio
		if [ x$grub_platform = xxen ]; then insmod xzio; insmod lzopio; fi
		insmod part_gpt
		insmod ext2
		search --no-floppy --fs-uuid --set=root bdcbe209-a589-47c6-9311-aee61f3ef2de
		echo	'Loading Linux 6.8.0-1025-gcp ...'
		if [ "${initrdfail}" = 1 ]; then
		  echo	'GRUB_FORCE_PARTUUID set, initrdless boot failed. Attempting with initrd.'
		  linux	/boot/vmlinuz-6.8.0-1025-gcp root=PARTUUID=b051c61f-d3ef-4e82-9463-c46f2810d974 ro  console=ttyS0,115200
		  echo	'Loading initial ramdisk ...'
		  initrd	/boot/initrd.img-6.8.0-1025-gcp
		else
		  echo	'GRUB_FORCE_PARTUUID set, attempting initrdless boot.'
		  linux	/boot/vmlinuz-6.8.0-1025-gcp root=PARTUUID=b051c61f-d3ef-4e82-9463-c46f2810d974 ro  console=ttyS0,115200 panic=-1
		fi
		initrdfail
	}
	menuentry 'Ubuntu, with Linux 6.8.0-1025-gcp (recovery mode)' --class ubuntu --class gnu-linux --class gnu --class os $menuentry_id_option 'gnulinux-6.8.0-1025-gcp-recovery-bdcbe209-a589-47c6-9311-aee61f3ef2de' {
		recordfail
		load_video
		insmod gzio
		if [ x$grub_platform = xxen ]; then insmod xzio; insmod lzopio; fi
		insmod part_gpt
		insmod ext2
		search --no-floppy --fs-uuid --set=root bdcbe209-a589-47c6-9311-aee61f3ef2de
		echo	'Loading Linux 6.8.0-1025-gcp ...'
		if [ "${initrdfail}" = 1 ]; then
		  echo	'GRUB_FORCE_PARTUUID set, initrdless boot failed. Attempting with initrd.'
		  linux	/boot/vmlinuz-6.8.0-1025-gcp root=PARTUUID=b051c61f-d3ef-4e82-9463-c46f2810d974 ro recovery nomodeset dis_ucode_ldr 
		  echo	'Loading initial ramdisk ...'
		  initrd	/boot/initrd.img-6.8.0-1025-gcp
		else
		  echo	'GRUB_FORCE_PARTUUID set, attempting initrdless boot.'
		  linux	/boot/vmlinuz-6.8.0-1025-gcp root=PARTUUID=b051c61f-d3ef-4e82-9463-c46f2810d974 ro recovery nomodeset dis_ucode_ldr  panic=-1
		fi
		initrdfail
	}
}
grub_cmd: echo GRUB_FORCE_PARTUUID set, attempting initrdless boot.
Exit Boot Services Returned with Success
